rps in December 1998 from Central Washington University  where he earned a Bachelor of Arts Degree in Law and Justice  Pre Law  Major Culp s assignments include company Executive Officer  Assistant Operations Officer and battalion S1  Okinawa  Japan  At the end of this tour  he received a branch transfer to the Military Police Corps and subsequently attended the MP Captain s Career Course at Fort Leonard Wood  Missouri  He then deployed with the 18th MP Brigade to Iraq in 2003 in support of Operation Iraqi Freedom 1  OIF 1  where he functioned as the brigade Battle Captain  This was followed by duties as a brigade Assistant S3 and Company Commander  560th MP Company  Mannheim  Germany  Beginning in September 2006  he served as the Aide de Camp to the CG  U S  Army CID Command  Fort Belvoir  Virginia followed by battalion S3  Washington CID Battalion  Fort Myer  Virginia  In 2008  Major Culp deployed in support of Operation Iraqi Freedom as the Detention Operations OIC for the Combined Joint Special Operations Task Force   Arabian Peninsula in Baghdad  Iraq  Upon redeployment  he attended Interagency Intermediate Level Education at Fort Belvoir  Virginia followed by a 12 month tour serving as an Interagency Fellow with the U S  Marshals Service  Arlington  Virginia  In August of 2010  Major Culp and family moved to Grafenwoehr  Germany where he assumed responsibilities as the battalion S3 with the 709th MP Battalion for over a year till he transitioned to the Executive Officer position which he filled until the spring of 2013  Major Culp is currently assigned as an Assistant Professor of Military Science and the MS II Branch Chief at the Virginia Military Institute  Major Culp is married to the former Heather Moore of Malott  Washington  They reside in Lexington  Virginia with their son Gunnar  18  and daughter Masyn  13  His hobbies include skiing  riding  Harley Road King Classic  camping  hiking  shooting  deer and elk hunting  and fishing  VMI Foundation Keydet C